{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6063b158-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1758"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1758"},"text":"§ 1758.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of royalty-in-kind revenue by Minerals Management Service","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"That in fiscal year 2006 and thereafter, the MMS may under the royalty-in-kind program, or under its authority to transfer oil to the Strategic Petroleum Reserve, use a portion of the revenues from royalty-in-kind sales, without regard to fiscal year limitation, to pay for transportation to wholesale market centers or upstream pooling points, to process or otherwise dispose of royalty production taken in kind, and to recover MMS transportation costs, salaries, and other administrative costs directly related to the royalty-in-kind program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6063b159-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/54/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–54, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-02"},"text":"Aug. 2, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/512"},"text":"119 Stat. 512","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6063b15a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6063b15b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6063b15c-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"MMS, referred to in text, means the Minerals Management Service.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6063b15d-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Department of the Interior, Environment, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 2006, and not as part of the Federal Oil and Gas Royalty Management Act of 1982 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6063b15e-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"similarProvisions","id":"id6063b15f-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Similar Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following prior appropriation acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/447/dE/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–447, div. E, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/3053"},"text":"118 Stat. 3053","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/108/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–108, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1255"},"text":"117 Stat. 1255","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/dF/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, div. F, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/229"},"text":"117 Stat. 229","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/63/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–63, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 2001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/428"},"text":"115 Stat. 428","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/291/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–291, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/932"},"text":"114 Stat. 932","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id6063b160-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6063b161-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Minerals Management Service was abolished and functions divided among the Office of Natural Resources Revenue, the Bureau of Ocean Energy Management, and the Bureau of Safety and Environmental Enforcement. See Secretary of the Interior Orders No. 3299 of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-05-19"},"text":"May 19, 2010","children":[],"tail":", and No. 3302 of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2010","children":[],"tail":", and chapters II, V, and XII of title 30, Code of Federal Regulations, as revised by final rules of the Department of the Interior at 75 F.R. 61051 and 76 F.R. 64432."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
